This paper deals with learning in models with discrete latent variables, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a modification to the continuous relaxation technique, which is a popular method in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The benchmark tasks used in the paper include generative modeling tasks, which are often related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of control variates, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
